zrow.ows_LinkTitle: Check writing scores in xml file
zrow.ows_Breif_x0020_Description:
NYS is claiming that writing scores for 3 students who tested online were never submitted in the xml file (see student details in attached files).
 
OAS Tier 3 team found the following - all these three students data came to OAS from ESH at
YONG-KE-SHI-0226  : 5/3/2014 
JUAN-CASTILLO-1011 : 5/3/2014
MARLON-BERNAL-0317 : 5/3/2014
 
The writing scores for these 3 students should have been included in the 6/13 xml file delivered to NYS.  This was a manual file for the date range 4/25 to 6/5. 
 
Question: were they in the file?
zrow.ows_Comments:
Xml file is generated based on the student updation date and not student creation date. Updation date is supposed to be changed whenever the student record is updated. Hence it cannot be determined the updation date of the student at the time the xml file was generated. Thus, from the database analysis we cannot say whether the student records were present in the xml file or not. We need the actual file to see if the student records are present in it or not.

4202 - Juan Castillo - 7/17/2014 1:19:11 PM
4203 - Marlon Bernal - 7/17/2014 1:18:21 PM
6239 - Yong Ke Shi - 7/17/2014 1:17:29 PM

zrow.ows_LinkTitle: Delayed Student Reports
zrow.ows_Breif_x0020_Description: The following examinees took a computer-based test at the Manhattan EOC on August 5, 2014. YORK HANDBERRY-UUID-000020074 NAKEEMA BOWE- UUID- 000019870 CTB sent us the records on both of these examinees in late August, but there were no scores in either file. Don’t know why CTB would send us a file without any scores….. We finally received the scores for both of these folks on December 5, 2014. Can you please find out why it took four (4) months for us to receive scores from a test session in August? If we are trying to convince applicants to take the CBT version and these CBT problems are continuing, we will have a hard time getting a large number of CBT testers. Why was there a 4 month delay in reporting these scores? What happened? Is this an issue that has affected more examinees than have been reported here?
zrow.ows_Comments:
Both the students took online test at August 5, 2014. Hence, the next weekly xml file NYTASCWEEKLY_STUDENTDATAFILE_20140815.xml contains the records for them. In the file, the scores were mentioned as "INV: Test Invalidated". When the status is INV then the xml file does not contain any score values.
 
If the status is toggled by OAS Administrator from Invalid to Valid state then the scores are populated in PRISM. On November 21, 2014 the scores for these two students were populated in PRISM. If student records are updated then PRISM resends the records in the next weekly xml file. So the next weekly xml file NYTASCWEEKLY_STUDENTDATAFILE_20141205.xml contains records for these two students.
 
Therefore, as the tests were Invalid, PSISM sent student records without scores. As OAS Administrator toggle validated the students after 4 months, PRISM resent student records with scores.

zrow.ows_LinkTitle: Prism data request for 2015 Annual Statistical Report
zrow.ows_Breif_x0020_Description:
We will need PRISM data for forms A,B,C,D,E,F, Spanish, English, Braille, Large print, and online and paper & pencil for all students who tested in 2015.
 
 
We want a comma delimited text file where there is one row per content area and test taken for a given examinee. The needed data is as follows:
ExamineeID
Examinee Last Name
Examinee First Name
Examinee Middle Initial
Examinee DOB
Gender
Ethnicity (resolved)
State
Highest Grade Completed
Language Version
Large Print
Braille
Mode of testing (p/p or online)
Content Area
Raw Score
Scale Score
Pass/Did not pass
Test Date for content area
Test Name
Test Form
Testing Center
If content area is Writing, Essay Raw score (0-8).

 
So, for a examinee that took all 5 content areas and passed on their first try, the file will have 5 records (5 rows).
For an examinee who took 3 tries to pass math, but passed all other 4 content areas on their first attempt, here will be a total of 7 records (7 rows).
 
Also to keep in mind, there is the additional criterion in Writing that they must also score at least a 2 (of 8) on the Essay and this we need the Final Essay raw score.
zrow.ows_Comments: Dear Parikshit, Thanks for you reply. The report has been prepared and the corresponding data exists in STUDENT_DETAILS_2015 table. Amit, Could you please take csv export of bellow mentioned query. SELECT * FROM STUDENT_DETAILS_2015 ORDER BY STATE_CODE, EXAMINEEID I have attached the query to populate the student details, please verify.

zrow.ows_LinkTitle: Addendum Prism data request for 2015 Annual Statistical Report
zrow.ows_Breif_x0020_Description:
We will need PRISM data for forms A,B,C,D,E,F, Spanish, English, Braille, Large print, and online and paper & pencil for all the 2014 students who tested any content area in 2015.   So, for each student that tested at least one content area in 2015, we will need to check to see if the student also tested 2014 and that 2014 data will need to be provided.  Note we have done a  similar request with similar layout for 2015 data  - Request # 438. I am assuming same Query could be utilized with some modifications

For the data we will be requesting, we need ALL scores for a given examinee as we will be providing metrics on first time test takers as well as all examinees in the categories of who tested, completed and passed these forms.
We want a comma delimited text file where there is one row per content area and test taken for a given examinee. The needed data is as follows:
ExamineeID
Examinee Last Name
Examinee First Name
Examinee Middle Initial
Examinee DOB
Gender
Ethnicity (resolved)
State
Highest Grade Completed
Language Version
Large Print
Braille
Mode of testing (p/p or online)
Content Area
Raw Score
Scale Score
Pass/Did not pass
Test Date for content area
Test Name
Test Form
Testing Center
If content area is Writing, Essay Raw score (0-8).
zrow.ows_Comments:
Logic behind that query as follows: 1. Identify the student with UUID and STATE_CODE 2. Check at least one test exist in 2015 3. Provide all test records of 2014 for that student.
PFA the data and query.
